ut I don't even see the reason for that, although it could be argued.<br>
<br>
Guilds like mine ( small, but good players ) can use Hate for EXP and upgrades for some characters.  We've gotten a couple upgrades already while receiving decent EXP.  The cash drops aren't too awful bad after paying for the port stones, but not that great that ubahs are going to farm the zone for cash.  Hate can now easily support 10 groups of 6 that are constantly EXPing.<br>
<br>
The &quot;bosses&quot; are TOUGH.  I don't know how they compare to some of the higher tier mobs, but I'd venture that they put the Kunark dragons to shame by a big margin.  This means that you're going to have to have a serious force to take them, and then you need to weigh risk -vs- reward.  Is it worth it to go camp/race for Inny or is it better to work on Vex Thal, etc, where you are getting many upgrades in the same amount of time it would take you to get just a couple?  I don't see the guilds that can make short work of Inny and Maestro wasting their time on them without good reason.  I don't know what these 2 are dropping, now, though so can't take that into account in my decision.<br>
<br>
Our guild hasn't seen en epic piece drop, yet, but I think that is what the vote will come down to - how it impacts the lower guilds' abililities to get their epic drops.  I don't think the ubahs care that much for most of the epics as a guild, although the members may still want to get them on their own time.<br>
<br>
Our guild hasn't taken a formal vote on what we think of keeping the rotation on Hate, but my guess is that it would be to leave it off of the rotations.<br>
<br>
Fear is another story.  I can't decide what makes the most sense ATM, and probably won't have a strong opinion unless it goes off of rotation and I see the impact after a couple months.  Haemish is correct that ubahs really don't give a crap about the armor drops there, but some may still want an epic piece or 3.  But, that means taking time out from Ssra, Vex Thal, NToV, PoP to gather for a Wraith of a Shissar kill.  Who knows, though - maybe they will try to monopolize these types of spawns, but at least with that particular spawn, it can't be MQd so they won't do it unless they have a chanter sans Epic and they're worried about getting everyone hasted FAST after a wipe.  Changing Fear is a tough call, but I wouldn't go against a majority on it.<br>
<br>
My assumption is Sony will see that changing Hate was a GoodIdea(tm) and do it for Fear within the next year and all of this will be moot. <p>Zymyool, Officer of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ancientadventurers.org"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Ancient Adventurers</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on the Karana Server<br>
